#Selvala's Charge (#1085): parley. Each reveal offers option one (token if nonland)
#and option two (put the card back); drive both for each player, then the draws.
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
manapool:{4}{G}
hand:selvala's charge
library:gold myr,millstone
[PLAYER2]
library:silver myr,juggernaut
[DO]
selvala's charge
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
choice 0
goto firstmain
choice 1
millstone
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
choice 0
goto firstmain
choice 1
juggernaut
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
[ASSERT]
FIRSTMAIN
[PLAYER1]
hand:millstone
graveyard:selvala's charge
inplay:*,*
library:gold myr
[PLAYER2]
hand:juggernaut
library:silver myr
[END]
#PARKED: the reveal menus drive (option one accepted, option two + click puts the
#card back, the afterrevealed draw fires for the caster) but option one's
#"if type(land|reveal)~lessthan~1 then _ELEPHANTTOKEN_" never creates the token even
#with a nonland revealed - the conditional-inside-optionone silently no-ops. The
#opponent's parley leg also stops after their reveal. Reveal-conditional engine item.
